<%# Shared COMMAND/SEARCH terminal-style input bar (R6/R7, architecture plan file/module
    layout table). This increment (Increment 3, COMMAND mode) wires the `:` command-entry
    path; a later increment (SEARCH, `/`) reuses this same partial/markup rather than
    standing up a second terminal-style bar -- only the leading glyph, placeholder copy,
    and controller-side wiring differ per mode.

    Plain-CSS `hidden` by default (nothing to flash without JS, matching the status
    line's own convention); keyboard_nav_controller#modeValueChanged() toggles visibility
    as COMMAND/SEARCH are entered/exited. The <input> is a real,
    <label class="sr-only">-labeled field (R11) -- never a focus trap. Enter/typing are
    wired as element-scoped Stimulus actions directly on the input (architecture plan
    Decision 2, rule 2) rather than document-level special cases; Esc is handled by the
    controller's existing document-level Escape branch (Increment 0), which already
    treats "mode !== normal" as "something of ours is open." %>
<div
  id="keyboard-command-bar"
  data-keyboard-nav-target="commandBar"
  class="hidden fixed bottom-0 inset-x-0 z-40 font-mono text-sm bg-base-200 text-base-content border-t border-base-300"
>
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-3 py-2 flex items-center gap-2">
    <label for="keyboard-command-input" class="sr-only">Command</label>
    <span aria-hidden="true" class="text-primary">:</span>
    <input
      type="text"
      id="keyboard-command-input"
      data-keyboard-nav-target="commandInput"
      data-action="input->keyboard-nav#handleCommandInput keydown.enter->keyboard-nav#commitCommand"
      autocomplete="off"
      autocapitalize="off"
      spellcheck="false"
      class="flex-1 bg-transparent outline-none"
      placeholder="home | writing | projects | resume | theme &lt;name&gt; | help"
    />
  </div>
  <div
    data-keyboard-nav-target="commandFeedback"
    aria-live="polite"
    class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-3 pb-2 text-xs text-base-content/60 empty:hidden"
  ></div>
</div>
